{
  "id": "019cdcdc-fd00-7850-9bc2-a02bfe9d03a9",
  "content": "`register_chunking()`.\n    pub fn prepare(&mut self, workspace_root: &str) {\n        let path = Path::new(workspace_root);\n        let map = crate::module_resolver::RustModuleMap::build(path);\n        self.module_map = Some(std::sync::Arc::new(map));\n    }\n}\n```\n\nUpdate the struct:\n```rust\npub struct GitAdapter {\n    module_map: Option<std::sync::Arc<crate::module_resolver::RustModuleMap>>,\n}\n```\n\nUpdate `register_chunking`:\n```rust\nfn register_chunking(&self, registry: &mut corvia_kernel::chunking_pipeline::FormatRegistry) {\n    use corvia_kernel::chunking_strategy::ChunkingStrategy;\n    use std::sync::Arc;\n    let ast = if let Some(ref map) = self.module_map {\n        Arc::new(crate::ast_chunker::AstChunker::with_module_map(Arc::clone(map)))\n    } else {\n        Arc::new(crate::ast_chunker::AstChunker::new())\n    };\n    for ext in ast.supported_extensions() {\n        registry.register_override(ext, ast.clone());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 5: Update CLI to call `adapter.prepare()` before `register_chunking()`**\n\nIn `corvia-cli/src/main.rs` `cmd_ingest` function (around line 455):\n\nChange:\n```rust\nlet adapter = GitAdapter::new();\n```\nTo:\n```rust\nlet mut adapter = GitAdapter::new();\nadapter.prepare(path);\n```\n\n**Step 6: Fix all existing tests that call `chunk_file_with_relations` without module_map**\n\nSearch for all calls to `chunk_file_with_relations` in tests and add `None` as the last parameter.\n\n**Step 7: Run all tests**\n\nRun: `cd /root/corvia-project/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia-adapter-git && cargo test`\nThen: `cd /root/corvia-project/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia && cargo test --workspace`\nExpected: All tests pass.\n\n**Step 8: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"feat(m3.4): integrate RustModuleMap into AstChunker and treesitter (D72)\"\n```\n\n---\n",
